race.comment: DESERT LIGHTNING (3) looks a big chance at decent odds. His first two runs this time in were excellent. He hit the front in the G1 Underwood Stakes two back but simply didn't run out 1800m behind the likes of Sir Delius and Buckaroo. Forgiving last time in the G1 Toorak Handicap as top weight when given a poor ride, wide without cover in a fast race. Back to set weights here, up on speed, he'll go close. RISE AT DAWN (4) has been good in two runs back from a spell. Fancy he went too slow in front last time having run much quicker early at Flemington. He's a horse that likes to be rolling and if that's the case, he goes close. GOLDEN PATH (5) is a tricky one to measure. He was poor in the G1 Turnbull Stakes but the G1 Underwood placing (albeit with things to suit) reads well. Back to a mile now is perhaps the niggle. OH TOO GOOD (8) had every favour last time but won well. Takes on the boys now but is a good mare and Lane gets the inside run again.
